title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer P938 Extreme & Extras
postcontent:
Many people have asked me for a price to sell this. I don't have a price since it is for trade only.  If you want to make an offer then go ahead but I am mainly looking to trade with or without cash on either end. I am considering mostly a trade for a S&W or Ruger stainless revolver ( like a SP101 ) or 1911 or anything in 10mm or maybe an AR.  But I don't want something someone pieced together themselves. but I would consider an offer if it is reasonable.

This is a Sig Sauer P938 Extreme. It has the original paperwork, lock, etc.  It has the 6rd mag & the 7 rd ext pinky mag.
I have shot this gun maybe 300rds.  I bought it and used it for concealed carry but it's a little on the small side for me and I am just ready for something different.  I do not work and only leave the house approximately once a week so it was not carried all day everyday. Also I had 2 foot surgeries this past year so I was laid up for at least 4 months. My point is it was carried lightly.
You can see the typical line on the top of the barrel which could be touched up with Duracoat but other than that it looks excellent.
Cleaned after every shot and stored in humidity controlled safe. Fingerprints always wiped off and lubed regularly.
The gun seemed a little plain in appearance to me so I had Omega Gunsmithing in Newport bead blast and Duracoat the barrel, hammer, take down pin, grip screws & amidex safety. My receipt shows this was done on July 26th, 2013.
Also I had a custom OWB holster made by Adams Leather Works in Texas (currently 10-12 week wait). WWW.ADAMSLEATHERWORKS.COM  The holster was stiff as all new leather is and its just finally starting to soften up probably from the lack of use.  You can watch a video of this guy make a holster from start to finish almost identical to this one on Youtube.  Here is a link:      http://youtu.be/mjr72-ANHq0   
I was so impressed with this mans skill I ordered my holster immediately and if I trade this P938 I will be ordering another from him.  He has a customer for life in me!
I just looked at the pics I posted for this ad and the holster didn't really come out as nice as it is in person.  He stains the leather then airbrushed black around all the edges. Sharp holster!

I paid $720 with the FFL fee for the Sig P938
$97.50 for Duracoating
& $80 for the holster
I realize it is used so not expecting a $900 trade value but I also am very aware of gun values so please don't waste your time with ridiculous offers or the junk in your safe that no one wants anyway. Mostly looking for a S&W revolver or maybe a Ruger like a SP101.  I also love 1911's and anything 10mm. No rifles, shotguns.
I also have a trade listing here on Armslist for a Springfield XDM 3.8 Compact 9mm Bi-Tone with everything it came with if anyone is interested in a larger trade.

I will delete this ad the minute it is gone, so no need to ask if I still have it.  If your reading this the answer is yes!
If interested send me a email or text.
Dan
734.threezeronine.ninetwofourtwo imessage available

I can send as many pics as you want.
